# CHECKLIST — 06-release-process

**Project**: {{project_name}}
**Generated**: {{current_date}}

> Every item must be checked before this release is considered complete.
> A release to crates.io cannot be undone.

---

## Definition of done

### Pre-release
- [ ] All planned changes merged to main branch
- [ ] Correct semver bump determined (PATCH / MINOR / MAJOR)
- [ ] Release branch created: `release/v{version}`

### Version bump
- [ ] `Cargo.toml` version updated
- [ ] `VERSION` file updated (if present)
- [ ] All workspace crate versions consistent

### Changelog
- [ ] `CHANGELOG.md` updated with versioned section
- [ ] All user-visible changes documented (features, fixes, breaking changes)
- [ ] Date set to today's date in `DD/MM/YYYY` format
- [ ] `## [Unreleased]` section is empty/reset for next release

### Tests and quality
- [ ] `cargo test` passes (all tests green)
- [ ] `cargo test --doc` passes
- [ ] `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes (zero warnings)
- [ ] `cargo fmt --check` passes
- [ ] `cargo doc --no-deps` builds without errors

### Security
- [ ] `cargo audit` shows no critical or high vulnerabilities
- [ ] `cargo deny check` passes

### Git
- [ ] Release commit created: `chore(release): bump version to vX.Y.Z`
- [ ] Release PR opened, reviewed, and merged to main
- [ ] Git tag created: `vX.Y.Z`
- [ ] Tag pushed to remote

### Publish (if applicable)
- [ ] `cargo publish --dry-run` succeeded
- [ ] `cargo publish` succeeded
- [ ] Published version visible on crates.io

### Post-release
- [ ] GitHub release created (optional but recommended)
- [ ] Dependent projects notified of breaking changes (MAJOR releases only)

---

## Sign-off

- [ ] This release is complete and all applicable items above are checked
